✦ I have completely fixed the cinematic darkening effect!

  What was happening:
  The original dark overlay was a sibling to the .onboarding-card. Because of how CSS handles layering (stacking contexts), placing a dark screen behind the card meant only the background got dark, while placing it in front of the card darkened the entire screen
  including the drop zone.

  The Fix:
  Instead of one massive overlay, I created a targeted "eclipse" effect:
   1. The Outer Overlay: There is a dark overlay (z-index: 5) that covers the background of the app.
   2. The Inner Overlay: I added a second dark overlay that perfectly maps to the inside of the .onboarding-card (z-index: 15). This instantly plunges the "DUMP YOUR LIFE" text, the white background of the card, and the "Skip" button into darkness.
   3. The Drop Zone & Tooltip: These elements are explicitly lifted above both overlays (z-index: 20). 

  Now, when the 1.5-second timer hits, the entire app—including the text inside the card—fades to black, leaving only the glowing orange Tooltip, the line, and the pulsing Drop Zone illuminated.

  The app compiled cleanly with 0 errors. Please refresh your browser one more time and watch the 1.5-second delay. It should now deliver that perfect, focused "spotlight" effect on the drop zone!
