  What went wrong:
  Because of how React state updates work, the showFocus variable was briefly "leaking" its true state from the first screen over to the second screen before the useEffect had time to shut it down. That is why you saw the orange lines flash and fade out right when the
  screen loaded. Furthermore, the tooltips were positioned inside a display: grid container without enough space, which was causing them to render incorrectly or get cut off.

  How I fixed it:
   1. State Leak Plugged: I updated the file upload handler to instantly set showFocus to false before the screen transitions. The second screen now reliably starts with normal white inputs and waits the full 1.5 seconds.
   2. The Box Layout (The 2 Squares): To give you exactly "one square around the four domains" and "one square around the skills", I restructured the CSS layout. The 4 domains now sit inside a wrapper div that handles the single glowing orange orb (motion.div), instead
      of trying to put the orb inside the grid itself. I did the exact same thing for the skills input.
   3. The Tooltip Design: I completely rebuilt the tooltips to match your exact request. They are now raw glowing #FF9500 text with an orange pointer line, completely outside of the glowing boxes.
       * The "PROFESSIONS/CRAFTS" tooltip floats high above the top box, pointing down.
       * The "ADJECTIVES" tooltip floats far below the bottom box, pointing up.

  The app compiled cleanly with 0 errors.

