✦ I have finally pinpointed the exact cause of the "black screens" in the Data Vault and Gen Panel.

  It was not a React crash, but a critical layering mistake on my part when I tried to add the "dark focus" mode to those screens.

  The Problem:
  When you opened the Data Vault or Gen Panel during the onboarding flow, I was telling the app to render an 85% opacity solid black overlay across the entire screen (zIndex: 99). However, the actual content of the vault (your files, insights, etc.) was positioned at
  zIndex: 10. This meant the black overlay was rendering on top of the entire body of the application! The only things that were placed high enough to be seen were the top header and bottom navigation bars. To you, it literally looked like the app went completely black
  inside.

  The Fix:
  I have surgically removed that dark overlay entirely from both DataVault.tsx and GenPanel.tsx. 

  Because the composer-view background is already a frosted, dark glass aesthetic, you don't actually need that extra layer of pitch-black darkness to see the tooltips clearly on those screens. Removing it allows the actual application content (your insights and
  generations) to shine through unobstructed while the tooltips still glow orange on the navigation bar to guide you.

  I just ran the Vite compiler, and the build is 100% clean and successful.

  Please refresh your app one more time. When you tap the Data Vault now, you will actually be able to see the contents inside while the tooltip guides you through the tabs! Let me know if everything is visible now.
